parameters:
Crew Member: It's tough with so much
luggage.

Rabi: The vast ocean that stretches on
forever!

Rabi: I want to try swimming at some
sandy beach!

Sachia: We came from the Imperial
Territory.

Sachia: My friend is a noble from the
Demon Continent, and we're about to go
play together.

Claudia: I love the sea. It reminds me
of my mother.
Claudia: Do you like the sea?

Zerachiel: Oh, that outfit... Are you an
adventurer, perhaps?
Rabi: The sea is so blue!

Sachia: Seriously, the view from the
ship is exceptional, right?!

Claudia: I'm used to seeing the sea, so
it's nothing...
Sachia: Ahaha, Claudia is so serious.

Sachia: In times like this, it's best to
just enjoy the flow.

Rabi: You seemed to be enjoying the
preparations for the trip more than
anyone else!

Sachia: Ahaha, seems like you hit the
mark.

Rabi: It's been a while since we had a
vacation, so let's have a lot of fun!

Sachia: I've been working non-stop, so
let's play once in a while.

Claudia: ...Yes, that's true. It's a
rare opportunity after all.

Claudia: Let's forget about work once in
a while.

Rabi: Fufufu, seems like I caused quite
a commotion! My apologies!

Zerachiel: Ah, no! I was just looking
because it seemed fun!
Sachia: Ahaha, sorry. I was being noisy.

Sachia: We're currently on a trip to the
Magic Continent. We might have gotten a
little carried away.
Claudia: Are you also on a trip?

Zerachiel: Y-Yeah, that might be the
feeling!!

Zerachiel: (I might not be good at
talking when there are a lot of
people...)

Claudia: Hehe, let's both enjoy
ourselves, shall we?

Claudia: I am Claudia, a magician who
works as an adventurer in the Empire.

Sachia: I'm Sachia, an adventurer just
like you.

Zerachiel: I am Zerachiel. I guess you
could say I'm like a traveler?

Claudia: Zerachiel... the name of one
who pledges loyalty to God.

Claudia: I wonder if you also believe in
God? By the way, I am a follower of the
destruction god, Fina--

Rabi: Claudia is a magic idiot, you
know...

Claudia: Is it the Beast God, Anri,
after all? The hero god who put an end
to the battle between the creation god
and the destruction god, how wonderful.

Claudia: Or perhaps you worship the evil
god Orpheus?

Claudia: There was a time when I also
infiltrated the cult to learn, because
there is a forbidden grimoire sleeping
there.

Claudia: The knowledge of the cult is
truly surprising, isn't it?

Zerachiel: (Claudia, you really are a
magic idiot...)
Rabi: Zerachiel seems to be in trouble.

Claudia: Oh, I'm sorry. When it comes to
talking about magic, I tend to forget
myself.

Claudia: Nice to meet you again,
Zerachiel.
